The captain was laughed at in all companies , and was ready to hang himself . 
After some time he recovered himself a little , and from that time became the most humble , the most modest , and most importunate man alive in his courtship . 
She carried her jest on a great way . 
She brought him by these tricks to submit to all possible measures to satisfy her , as well of his circumstances as of his behaviour . 
It was enough to him to obtain her for a wife . 
But I come now to my own case , in which there was at this time no little nicety . 
In short , the widow , they said , had no money . 
In the next place , she tells her husband that I had at least fortune , and that after some of my relations I was like to have a great deal more . 
It was enough to tell her husband this there needed nothing on my side . 
I picked out my man without much difficulty , by the judgment I made of his way of courting me . 
He stopped my mouth in that part with the thunder of his protestations , as above , but still I pretended to doubt . 
One morning he pulls off his diamond ring , and writes upon the glass of the sash in my chamber this line 'You I love , and you alone . 
I read it , and asked him to lend me his ring , with which I wrote under it , thus 'And so in love says every one . 
He takes his ring again , and writes another line thus 'Virtue alone is an estate . 
I borrowed it again , and I wrote under it 'But money's virtue , gold is fate . 
I ventured all upon the last cast of poetry , as you'll see , for I wrote boldly under his last 'I'm poor let's see how kind you'll prove . 
This was a sad truth to me whether he believed me or no , I could not tell I supposed then that he did not . 
I took his pen , and followed him immediately , thus 'Yet secretly you hope I lie . 
I wrote again 'She loves enough that does not hate . 
'Very well , thought I 'you shall carry me thither as soon as you please , though I won't tell you so beforehand . 
All this , you may be sure , was as I wished , and indeed nothing could have happened more perfectly agreeable . 
