I cast about innumerable ways for my future state of life , and began to consider very seriously what I should do , but nothing offered . 
But all this was nothing I found no encouraging prospect . 
I waited I lived regularly , and with as much frugality as became my circumstances , but nothing offered , nothing presented , and the main stock wasted apace . 
What to do I knew not the terror of approaching poverty lay hard upon my spirits . 
I had some money , but where to place it I knew not , nor would the interest of it maintain me , at least not in London . 
At length a new scene opened . 
This perplexed me strangely , and what to do I knew not . 
He added , that his friend should take nothing of me for his advice or assistance , and this indeed encouraged me very much . 
He appointed the same evening , after the bank was shut and business over , for me to meet him and his friend . 
Accordingly I met him the next day , when I entered more freely with him into my case . 
I began to think he had been in the condition of my late lover , and that his wife had been distempered or lunatic , or some such thing . 
I told him I would come , and desired to know where he lived . 
He smiled and , standing up , with great respect saluted me . 
He told me I was wrong . 
'I know nothing of your circumstances that way , sir , said I 'but it cannot be innocent to wish your wife dead . 
'I tell you , says he again , 'she is a wife and no wife you don't know what I am , or what she is . 
'Well , well , says he , 'and so I am , I hope , too . 
but I am something else too , madam for , says he , 'to be plain with you , I am a cuckold , and she is a whore . 
Well , I pitied him , and wished him well rid of her , and still would have talked of my business , but it would not do . 
At last he looks steadily at me . 
'Well , sir , says I , 'then you must divorce her . 
If you can prove what you say , you may certainly get that done , and then , I suppose , you are free . 
'That's very tedious and expensive , says he . 
