I had no more spirit left in me , I had no tongue to speak , or eyes to look up either to God or man . 
It is rather to be thought of than expressed what was now my condition . 
In the meantime my poor distressed governess sent me a minister , who at her request first , and at my own afterwards , came to visit me . 
It was now that , for the first time , I felt any real signs of repentance . 
The word eternity represented itself with all its incomprehensible additions , and I had such extended notions of it , that I know not how to express them . 
But I go back to my own case . 
The minister pressed me to tell him , as far as I though convenient , in what state I found myself as to the sight I had of things beyond life . 
This honest , friendly way of treating me unlocked all the sluices of my passions . 
He broke into my very soul by it and I unravelled all the wickedness of my life to him . 
In a word , I gave him an abridgment of this whole history I gave him a picture of my conduct for fifty years in miniature . 
A terrible blow this was to my new resolutions indeed my heart sank within me , and I swooned away twice , one after another , but spoke not a word . 
Such , however , will , I hope , allow me the liberty to make my story complete . 
But I go on with my relation . 
